  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The study sponsor has developed a patented medical device called Seipher Wellness. This is a
      non-invasive medical device that assesses heart health based on established cardiac
      parameters; timing events of the cardiac cycle. These are specific parameters captured and
      analyzed by the device. A ratio of two specific timing parameters provides an assessment of
      the subject's overall heart health. The aim of this study is to validate the device algorithm
      across a range of subjects.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
